<section class="mainBodyText u-StructureWrapper sidePadding50 paddingRight">
    <h2>General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)</h2>
<p>Edinburgh Napier University is, and always has been, committed to respecting your privacy and protecting your personal information. We have had policies, procedures and privacy notices in place under the Data Protection Act 1998 for many years now and have been busy since 2016 enhancing these to comply with the new General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the new UK Data Protection Act 2018.</p>
<p>For more information on what information we use and how we collect and use it, please see our Data Protection pages using the following links:</p>
<ul>
    <li><a href="http://staff.napier.ac.uk/dataprotection" target="_blank">Data Protection Policy statement and Code of Practice</a></li>
    <li><a href="http://staff.napier.ac.uk/dpstatements" target="_blank">Privacy Notices</a></li>
</ul>
<p>If you have any questions regarding the use of your personal data or want to know more about your rights under the legislation or how the University complies with the legislation please contact the Data Protection Officer at <a href="mailto:dataprotection@napier.ac.uk">dataprotection@napier.ac.uk</a>.</p>

    

